Oh, and, I also got a thank you card from a student nurse today in which she wrote ‘You are a wonderful nurse - I hope I can be like you.’ 13 hour shifts are so long that I forgot this happened at 9am. So, maybe I nearly cried at work twice today lol.
All in all, although tough at times, today was a good day, and I can genuinely say I think I was a good nurse today, showing compassion and advocating for my patient.
I don’t know why some things hit emotionally when others don’t, I’ve had sicker patients and other tough situations which haven’t affected me, but today got me.
Instead of crying, I liaised with the MDT and together we curated a new plan which would hopefully be more ethical for the patient and cause less distress.
